<div data-site-mode-only="launch">
  <section class="hero hero--image launch-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero__inner">
        <div class="hero__content">
          <span class="hero__eyebrow">i-Pace Owners' Advocacy Group</span>
          <h1 class="hero__title">I-PACE owners working together for fair outcomes</h1>
          <p class="hero__subtitle">
            We are an independent group of Jaguar I-PACE owners who want to engage constructively with JLR.
          </p>
          <p class="hero__subtitle">
          Register and help shape a fair and consistent resolution for us all.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__ctas">
            <a href="/join/" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Join the Group</a>
          </div>
          <p class="launch-hero__note">Free to join. It takes less than a minute.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="hero__media">
          <img src="/images/ipace-hero.png"
            alt="A dark electric SUV on a quiet road, representing Jaguar I-PACE owners working together" width="1738"
            height="905">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Launch Why now? -->
  <section class="section launch-purpose">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="launch-kicker">Why now?</p>
      <h2>Recalls and traction battery failures need an organised response</h2>
      <p class="text-muted why-now__intro">
        Many owners face the same set of problems. For now, the task is simple:
        register enough owners to show JLR there is an organised UK group ready to engage.
      </p>

      <div class="two-column launch-why-grid" style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">
        <div class="stack stack--sm">

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>H447 / H570 / H571 / H572 campaigns</strong> — owner
              experiences around notification, booking times and outcomes
              vary during the ongoing UK and international recall campaigns.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Traction battery faults</strong> — spontaneous power loss and capacity limiting,
              traction faults, warning lights, and loss of vehicle performance affecting a large number of owners.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="stack stack--sm">

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Approaching the 8-year / 100,000-mile battery warranty</strong>
              — Many I-PACEs will soon reach the end of their HV battery warranty period,
              raising urgent questions about long-term support and possible future costs.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Inconsistent experiences</strong> — owners have differing
              outcomes on loan cars, parts delays, goodwill payments, and
              warranty responsibility mean some owners receive fair treatment
              while others do not.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="callout callout--info launch-registration-callout">
        <span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
        <div class="callout__content">
          <p class="callout__title">This is an advocacy group, not another forum</p>
          <p>Our purpose is to understand what owners need, represent those views clearly,
            and pursue a fair and consistent resolution. We are not building an open comment
            board or a place for fragmented settlement demands.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-muted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid--2 launch-route-grid">
        <article class="card card--accent">
          <p class="launch-kicker">Our preferred route</p>
          <h2 class="card__title">A constructive agreement</h2>
          <div class="card__body">
            <p>We want JLR to engage with an organised group of registered owners early,
              understand the range of owner preferences, and reach a broadly acceptable
              solution before Jaguar's next vehicle launch. A prompt, positive outcome would
              benefit owners, JLR, and confidence in the brand.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <p class="launch-kicker">If that route fails</p>
          <h2 class="card__title">Owners keep their options</h2>
          <div class="card__body">
            <p>An organised group is prepared to consider other appropriate routes if
              constructive engagement does not succeed. We have legal counsel within the group
              to help test the process and options, but joining now does not enrol you in legal
              action. Any future proposal would be explained separately, and each owner would
              choose whether to take part.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section launch-final-cta">
    <div class="container container--narrow text-center">
      <h2>Add your voice</h2>
      <p>Membership helps us show that UK I-PACE owners are organised, aligned, and ready
        to engage constructively. For now, we are only asking owners to register with a name
        and email address.</p>
      <a href="/join/" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Join the Group</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

