  <!-- Why now? -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why now?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted why-now__intro">
        I-PACE owners face a converging set of challenges that make collective
        action timely and important.
      </p>

      <div class="two-column" style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">
        <div class="stack stack--sm">

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Traction battery faults</strong> — spontaneous power
              loss, warning lights, and loss of vehicle performance affecting
              a significant number of owners.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>H447 / H570 / H571 / H572 campaigns</strong> — ongoing DVSA
              and international recall campaigns with varying owner
              experiences around notification, booking times and outcomes.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>HV battery work and module replacements</strong> —
              some owners receive new modules or a full battery; others
              receive software updates only. Outcomes are inconsistent.
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="stack stack--sm">
          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Battery State of Health concerns</strong> — degradation
              beyond what owners consider acceptable, with limited transparency
              about what JLR considers normal.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Approaching the 8-year / 100,000-mile battery warranty</strong>
              — many I-PACEs are now entering or beyond the original battery
              warranty period, raising urgent questions about long-term support.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="why-item">
            <div class="why-item__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Inconsistent owner experiences</strong> — differing
              outcomes on loan cars, parts delays, goodwill payments, and
              warranty responsibility mean some owners receive fair treatment
              while others do not.
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

